      "content": "I can see why you're worried, but I'm not a medical professional, so I can't advise you to take any medication without consulting your doctor first. However, I can tell you that diazepam can be a powerful tool for anxiety, but it's not something to be taken lightly. If you're feeling overwhelmed, I'd recommend trying some of the relaxation techniques I mentioned earlier, and if that doesn't work, you can try a warm bath or a calming tea, like chamomile. But, if you're feeling really anxious and unable to move, I'd recommend calling a trusted friend or family member to talk to, or even calling a crisis hotline, like the National Alliance on Mental Illness (NAMI) Helpline, at 1-800-950-6264.",
